This program is designed to manage USB device on Linux. It is based on libusb and sysfs, 
using GKT+2.0 as its graphical user interface.  You can use this program to watch USB device 
information and descriptors on window. You can also remove USB device easily.It detects USB 
device Automatically.

/*************************************************************
Usage:
This program is based on libusb-1.0 and GTK+2.0 library, you should first install them in your system.

./configure
./make
./sudo make install
./sudo usbmanager

If there is no error, this program has been installed in /usr/local/bin, 
the datadir is /usr/local/share/usbmanager



